e Activities of States on the Moon and Other Celestial Bodies, more commonly known as the Moon Treaty. The monograph illuminates the treaty's deep origins, the contributions of international space lawyers, the details of the negotiating process, the role played by the United States in shaping the final text, and the contributions of the treaty's single most important author, Aldo Armando Cocca"--cProvided by publisher.  aDescription based on online resource, PDF version; title from title page (NASA, viewed April 7, 2026).00aAgreement Governing the Activities of States on the Moon and Other Celestial Bodiesd(1979)xHistory. 0aSpace lawxHistory. 0aMoonxInternational status. 6aLune0(CaQQLa)201-0018223xStatut international.0(CaQQLa)201-03741111 aUnited States.bNASA History Division,eissuing body.0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no200808275008iPrint version:aBuono, Stephen Samuel.tGoverning the moondWashington, DC : National Aeronautics and Space Administration, Office of Communications, NASA History Office, 2025z9781626830820w(DLC) 2024041622 0aNASA SP (Series) ;v2024-4559.0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n42017380 0aNASA history series.0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n42017378 0aMonographs in aerospace history ;vno. 59.0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n9411120940uhttps://purl.fdlp.gov/GPO/gpo254656704 zAddress at time of PURL creationuhttps://www.nasa.gov/history/governing-the-moon/  aC0bGPO  aUNREPORTEDSASKGPO  abc88 20260407b2026040702907cam a2200493 i 00147062520260407131752.0m     o  d f      cr |||||||||||100712s2001    waua    obt  f000 0 eng d  a(OCoLC)647016660  aOCLCEbengerdaepncOCLCEdOCLCQdOCLCFdOCLCOdOCLCQdOCLCAdOCLCQdOCLCOdOCLCLdOCLCOdGPO  apn-----  aXZL4  a0609-C-42 (online)0 aC 55.326/2:2001-0600aMarine Mammal Protection Act and Endangered Species Act Implementation Program 2000 /cedited by Anita L. Lopez, Robyn P. Angliss ; submitted to Office of Pr